name: Bumi Linggah Villas Bali
address: Jl. Pasekan Jl. Raya Banjar Tubuh, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1:
We were here last week for 2 nights. It was really good experience. Villa was beautiful. Swimming pool was clean. We enjoyed.

Pros-
1. Quick room service.
2. Very clean.
3. Polite and kind staff.
4. We get Indian chai. It's rare to get Indian chai in Bali.

Cons-
1. Same breakfast everyday!
2. Lizards everywhere. Especially in dinning hall. Beside the food tray, on the plates, spoons. This was the worst part !
review 2:
Located in silent place away from city rush and crowd, you can find peace here. Surrounded by greenery all over the villas you will get forest vibe  and will find yourself in the middle of forest.

In villas, you will have a private pool (although not that big) enough for 2, private hall for lunch and watch tv (No channels were available) and private bedroom with attached washroom having jacuzzi.

Food options is limited & you will find insects because of greenery (JUST BE AWARE). Rest everything was perfect during my stay.
review 3: Rooms are in dire need of renovation. Glass door came out of panel. Luckily we were not hurt. One chair broke when one of us sat on it. Very poor quality furniture. Bathroom area is dirty and not well maintained. Staff are good, cooperative and ready to help. Breakfast menu has no variety.
review 4:
The villa is perfect for stay. The staff was very friendly. We required Jain food, so the staff immediately made us something available, suitable to us. They were very friendly and helpful to us.

However there were red ants, flies and earworms all over inside the villa, especially in the bathroom area. The house villa is fluorished with greeneries, that might be the reason. But it was nearly impossible to move freely in bathroom area. Some maintenance needs to be addressed to the plants and trees as it was a hurdle for sitting nearby the pool.

Also there are supermarkets nearby, making it a good location.
review 5: No maintenance... rooms are different from what shown on booking process..old furniture..less light at night very scary.. pools are not good..just do not book by website photos.. actually the villas are not maintained..wasted my 2 days in these property.... disappointed üòî

name: NAD Coffee & Eatery
address: Jl. Pd. Batu Alam No.26, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
really beautiful quiet place, perfect for working or just enjoying the view with delicious coffee and food. The staff is super friendly and welcoming.
Air conditioning perfectly tempered and possible to pay with card.
Totally recommended :)

review 3: I like this place, especially the co-working space area which is really comfortable and cool with views of the river and bamboo fields. This is really a suitable place to work while healing. I will visit this place often. About the food, there's no doubt everything is delicious! üë®üèª‚Äçüíªüëåüèª
review 4: NAD Coffee & Eatery is a delightful gem! The cozy atmosphere and friendly staff make it a perfect spot for a casual hangout or a quick bite. The coffee here is exceptional, brewed to perfection and accompanied by a charming selection of eats. The menu caters to various tastes, ensuring there's something for everyone. What adds to the charm is the welcoming ambiance, making it a great place to unwind. If you're in the area and in need of a coffee fix or a tasty meal, NAD Coffee & Eatery is a must-visit. Highly recommended for coffee enthusiasts and foodies alike!
review 5: A hidden gem in the suburb, this cafe offers affordable yet scrumptious mains, snacks and drinks. There's a stream running behind this cafe, perfectly blending nature into its atmosphere just like its catchphrase "NADTURE". If you're looking for the perfect place to end your evening right, this is where you should be. Very friendly owner and staff too.

name: Mepantigan Bali
address: Jl. Pasekan, Jl. Pd. Batu Alam Jl. Raya Banjar Tubuh No.30, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: Incredible experience, this is a must try being in Bali.  Very friendly guys from the Mepatingan Bali team will help you to relax and free your madness outside.  The traditional martial arts of Bali imply a fight in the mud, which is incredibly fun!  This is a very cool place with a relaxing atmosphere.  In addition to fighting practice and dancing, you will receive a sauna, a relaxing massage and a delicious meal and coffee.  Highly recommend!  There were even Kim Kardashian and David Copperfield, try it and you!
review 2: I visited as part of a school trip and the children loved it! All the staff were very attentive and friendly. Both teachers and Children were very well looked after. I could see the place was used to having school programs as all activities were very engaging and the transition between the games were very smooth. The staff were very accommodating and the place was fully equipped. Overall a fantastic day! I highly recommend! Thank you
review 3:
Best mud, best staff in Bali

Wear long pants and sleeves if mosquitoes like you
review 4: Warung theso is one of classic warung at angseri village  on way to natural hotspring  angseri. At warung theso you can try best test of bali combination of western  food witch healty style and simple lifestyle  and use power of love, so come and try warungtheso  food at angseri baturiti tabanan
review 5: The place all natural and simple, all the guru (coaches nor teachers) are friendly nice polite, the owners so humble. When the 1st time I came here (recommended by close friend) they look after me and my boy, as a new comer makes me feel welcome, they also train my boy how to do archery and how to ride a horse properly
